President Obama has announced his intent to appoint Julia A. Pierson as the Director of the United States Secret Service. Pierson has over 30 years of experience with the Secret Service and has held various leadership roles within the agency. She is currently serving as the Chief of Staff in the Office of the Director of the United States Secret Service. President Obama praised Pierson's dedication and qualifications, stating that her experiences will guide her in leading the men and women of the agency in safeguarding Americans and protecting leaders and first families. Pierson joined the Secret Service in 1983 as a Special Agent in Miami and has also served as a police officer in the Orlando Police Department. She holds a B.A. from the University of Central Florida.